tac.machine

Enum InstrName

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<InstrName>
      • tac.machine.InstrName
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<InstrName>

    public enum InstrName
extends java.lang.Enum<InstrName>
    Abstract machine instruction names.
    MOVE r1 r2 : copy contents of reg[r2] into reg[r1]
    LOAD r1 r2 : copy contents of mem[reg[r2]] into reg[r1]
    LOADI r n : copy integer n into reg[r]
    STORE r1 r2 : copy contents of reg[r1] into mem[reg[r2]]
    LT r1 r2 r3: set reg[r1] to 1 if reg[r2] less than reg[r3], 0 otherwise
    LE r1 r2 r3: set reg[r1] to 1 if reg[r2] less than or equal reg[r3], 0 otherwise
    EQ r1 r2 r3: set reg[r1] to 1 if reg[r2] equal reg[r3], 0 otherwise
    ADD r1 r2 r3 : set reg[r1] to reg[r2] + reg[r3]
    SUB r1 r2 r3 : set reg[r1] to reg[r2] - reg[r3]
    MUL r1 r2 r3 : set reg[r1] to reg[r2] * reg[r3]
    DIV r1 r2 r3 : set reg[r1] to reg[r2] / reg[r3]
    JMP r : jump to instruction at location reg[r]
    JMPI n : jump to instruction at location n
    CJMP r1 r2 : if reg[r1] is 0, jump to instruction at location reg[r2], else do nothing
    CJMPI r n : if reg[r] is 0, jump to instruction at location n, else do nothing
    JMPAL r : set reg[RET] = reg[PC], jump to instruction at location reg[r]
    JMPALI n : set reg[RET] = reg[PC], jump to instruction at location n
    SYSCALL n : execute system call number n
    NOOP : do nothing
